Fix SIGSEGV in evdi_open_attached_to() when called with a NULL parent device.

The SMIUSBDisplayManager daemon calls the deprecated evdi_open_attached_to(NULL)
to obtain a generic EVDI device. In libevdi 1.15 this wrapper passes the pointer
straight into strlen() before evdi_open_attached_to_fixed() gets a chance to
handle the NULL case (which it does, via get_generic_device()). strlen(NULL)
dereferences address 0 and crashes the daemon in its pnpThreadfunc thread every
time a monitor is plugged in.

Guard the NULL so length becomes 0 and _fixed() takes its NULL path.

--- a/library/evdi_lib.c
+++ b/library/evdi_lib.c
@@ -639,7 +639,8 @@
 // deprecated, use evdi_open_attached_to_fixed
 evdi_handle evdi_open_attached_to(const char *sysfs_parent_device)
 {
-	return evdi_open_attached_to_fixed(sysfs_parent_device, strlen(sysfs_parent_device));
+	return evdi_open_attached_to_fixed(sysfs_parent_device,
+		sysfs_parent_device ? strlen(sysfs_parent_device) : 0);
 }

 evdi_handle evdi_open_attached_to_fixed(const char *sysfs_parent_device, size_t length)
